// The FFI memory boundary's exported type. `rawptr` is an INERT machine address — just an `i64`, with no
// memory semantics (no deref/index/length). The only operation that interprets one as memory is `mem.bound`
// (see mem.arche), which forms a checked slice. Modeling it as an i64 alias makes "bound is the only flow"
// structural, not a lint: an integer simply has no other way to become memory.
rawptr :: i64;
